The Prague transport companies also transport on a chip for the first time on Wednesday
Wednesday, 1 October 2008, will go down in the history of Prague's transport operations as a date on which the first passengers to enter a subway, tram or bus will carry an electronic coupon in their pocket instead of a paper ticket.
These can currently be purchased by about one hundred thousand people who own the chip card Opencard.
Passengers can buy a 30-day, a 90-day or an annual coupon (valid from 1 January 2009) and play it on their chip card at the same time, in the information centers and branches of the transport companies at the metro stations Muzeum, M<0xC5><0xAF>stek, N<0xC3><0xA1>dra<0xC5><0xBE><0xC3><0xAD> Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice, And<0xC4><0x9B>l, Roztyly, Ratylysany, Letryby, Ratylysany.
