Foreign travel ban for Gary Glitter
Gary Glitter, the glam rock star who was convicted of child sexual abuse, has been banned from travelling to France and Spain.
Judges imposed a six-month ban on Glitter after he informed the authorities that he wanted to travel to Spain via France.
Kent police were granted a travel ban last Thursday after presenting evidence to the judges of Glitter’s convictions for sexual abuse of children.
Glitter, real name Paul Gadd, did not attend the hearing at the Ashford District Court in Kent, but was represented by Corker Binning Law Firm.
