Some children talk at night
I do not mean those who wake up and tell us something about what happened the day before, but the children who talk during sleep.
If it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality it does not matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder, which is called talking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Surely, more than one of you has been told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in a lifetime, for example, as during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can not remember anything.
There is not a single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often, relationships are sought with other phenomena in sleep, such as nightmares, panic at night, enuresis noctura (sleep-wetting at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we have mentioned before, it can be very high fiber, stressful situations or overwork.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that you speak calmly in single words, whisper or it may be quite the opposite (crying, crying, long discussions ).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and consult with a specialist to check if there is a problem that causes fear and thus occurs.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is to carry out a series of simple preventive measures:
Do not try to excite the child before going to sleep.
So, choose quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV programs that are terrible and a little too wild.
For the nervous children who are advised to relax, relaxation methods can be used to help them get some inner peace.
This helps the child to sleep peacefully.
